  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Outpainting extends an image beyond its original borders by generating new content that continues the scene. Under the hood it is a special case of inpainting: the mask covers the empty canvas region rather than an interior region, and the model must extrapolate texture, perspective, and lighting from the visible edge pixels. Because a single inpainting pass can only extend a canvas reliably by about 20–30% before quality degrades, production outpainting always uses an iterative slide-and-fill strategy — extending one window at a time and compositing each step back before continuing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Outpainting as Exterior Inpainting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The only structural difference between inpainting and outpainting is the position of the mask. In inpainting the mask targets pixels inside the frame; in outpainting it targets pixels outside the original frame on an extended canvas."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The canvas extension sequence:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Create a new blank canvas of the target size (e.g. 2048×512 for a 4× horizontal extension)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Paste the original image at the anchor position (e.g. left edge, centred vertically)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Build a mask: white (255) in the empty region, black (0) where the original image sits, with a Gaussian-blurred feather zone (64–128 px) at the boundary."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Crop a 512×512 window that straddles the boundary (half original, half new canvas). Run inpainting on this window."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Paste the generated pixels onto the canvas — but always re-paste the original image on top to prevent drift in previously established regions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Shift the window by ",
                    "marks": []
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "step_size",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " pixels and repeat until the entire target canvas is filled."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Iterative outpainting: original image extended right in 25% steps, with each step pasted back before the next window is inpainted"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Core Outpainting Pipeline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import numpy as np\nfrom PIL import Image\nfrom diffusers import StableDiffusionInpaintPipeline\nimport torch\nfrom scipy.ndimage import gaussian_filter\n\npipe = StableDiffusionInpaintPipeline.from_pretrained(\n    \"runwayml/stable-diffusion-inpainting\",\n    torch_dtype=torch.float16,\n).to(\"cuda\")\n\ndef outpaint_right(\n    original: Image.Image,\n    target_width: int,\n    prompt: str,\n    negative_prompt: str = \"low quality, blurry\",\n    step_size: int = 128,   # pixels shifted per iteration\n    feather_px: int = 64,   # blur radius for mask edge\n    window: int = 512,\n    num_steps: int = 40,\n    guidance_scale: float = 8.0,\n) -> Image.Image:\n    H, W = original.height, original.width\n    orig_np = np.array(original.convert(\"RGB\"))\n\n    # 1. Build extended canvas (filled with edge-replicated colour)\n    canvas = np.zeros((H, target_width, 3), dtype=np.uint8)\n    canvas[:, :W] = orig_np\n    canvas[:, W:] = orig_np[:, -1:, :]  # replicate right edge colour\n\n    # 2. Track which pixels are \"original\" (never overwrite these)\n    orig_mask = np.zeros((H, target_width), dtype=np.float32)\n    orig_mask[:, :W] = 1.0\n\n    # 3. Slide window from where original ends toward target\n    x = W - window // 2  # start: window half over original, half into new region\n    while x + window <= target_width:\n        # Crop window from canvas\n        crop = Image.fromarray(canvas[:, x:x+window])\n\n        # Build mask: 1 = inpaint (new region), 0 = preserve (original)\n        mask_1d = 1.0 - orig_mask[:, x:x+window]\n        # Feather at the left edge of the new region\n        mask_blurred = gaussian_filter(mask_1d, sigma=feather_px / 3)\n        mask_blurred = np.clip(mask_blurred, 0, 1)\n        mask_img = Image.fromarray((mask_blurred * 255).astype(np.uint8), mode=\"L\")\n\n        # Run inpainting\n        result = pipe(\n            prompt=prompt,\n            negative_prompt=negative_prompt,\n            image=crop,\n            mask_image=mask_img,\n            strength=1.0,\n            guidance_scale=guidance_scale,\n            num_inference_steps=num_steps,\n        ).images[0]\n\n        # Paste result back\n        result_np = np.array(result)\n        canvas[:, x:x+window] = result_np\n\n        # Always restore original pixels to prevent drift\n        canvas[:, :W] = orig_np\n\n        x += step_size\n\n    return Image.fromarray(canvas)\n\n\n# Extend a 512-wide landscape to 1536 px wide\nimage = Image.open(\"landscape.png\").convert(\"RGB\").resize((512, 512))\nwide = outpaint_right(\n    original=image,\n    target_width=1536,\n    prompt=\"mountain valley landscape, misty morning, photorealistic, seamless\",\n)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Multi-Direction Extension"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To expand in multiple directions (left, right, up, down), extend one direction at a time and re-anchor the original after each pass. Order matters: extending right then left produces better seams than trying to expand all four sides simultaneously, because each completed edge provides context for the next."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def outpaint_all_directions(\n    original: Image.Image,\n    pad_left: int,\n    pad_right: int,\n    pad_top: int,\n    pad_bottom: int,\n    prompt: str,\n) -> Image.Image:\n    W, H = original.size\n    target_W = W + pad_left + pad_right\n    target_H = H + pad_top + pad_bottom\n\n    # Create padded canvas with original centred\n    canvas = Image.new(\"RGB\", (target_W, target_H), (128, 128, 128))\n    canvas.paste(original, (pad_left, pad_top))\n\n    # Extend right\n    if pad_right > 0:\n        canvas = outpaint_right(canvas, target_W, prompt)\n    # Extend left (flip, outpaint right, flip back)\n    if pad_left > 0:\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.FLIP_LEFT_RIGHT)\n        canvas = outpaint_right(canvas, target_W, prompt)\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.FLIP_LEFT_RIGHT)\n    # Extend down (rotate, outpaint right, rotate back)\n    if pad_bottom > 0:\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.ROTATE_90)\n        canvas = outpaint_right(canvas, target_H, prompt)\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.ROTATE_270)\n    # Extend up\n    if pad_top > 0:\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.FLIP_TOP_BOTTOM)\n        canvas = outpaint_right(canvas, target_H, prompt)\n        canvas = canvas.transpose(Image.FLIP_TOP_BOTTOM)\n\n    return canvas"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Anchoring for Coherent Extensions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The most common outpainting failure is when the generated extension drifts stylistically or spatially from the original. The prompt must describe what is already visible, not just what should be added."
          }
        ]
      },
